IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SEEKING TO PUT GOD'S LOVE INTO ACTION, PENSACOLA HABITAT FOR HUMANITY BRINGS PEOPLE TOGETHER TO BUILD HOMES, COMMUNITIES, AND HOPE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO BUILD HOUSES AND IMPROVE COMMUNITIES IN PARTNERSHIP WITH LOW TO MODERATE INCOME FAMILIES IN ESCAMBIA COUNTY AND SANTA ROSA COUNTY, FLORIDA
IRS990.Desc: COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM - BUILT OR REHABBED AND SOLD 35 HOMES TO FAMILIES UNDER 80% AMI. COMPLETED 40 CRITICAL HOME REPAIRS, 7 WHEELCHAIR RAMPS, 1 COMMUNITY GARDEN, AND 3 DISASTER RESPONSES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: PENSACOLA HABITAT FOR HUMANITY RESTORE - DIVERTED 836 TONS FROM THE LANDFILL AND HAD 2084 NEW DONORS CONTRIBUTE TO THE MISSION OF BUILDING HOMES, COMMUNITIES, AND HOPE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HOMEOWNER ESCROW FUNDS TO COVER DUAL-SIGNATURE INSURANCE CLAIM CHECKS TO BE DISBURSED AS REPAIR WORK IS COMPLETED.

THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND FLORIDA STATUTES SECTION 220.13(2). HOWEVER, INCOME FROM CERTAIN ACTIVITIES NOT DIRECTLY RELATED TO THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSE IS SUBJECT TO TAXATION AS UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. MANAGEMENT IS NOT AWARE OF ANY TRANSACTIONS THAT WOULD NEGATIVELY IMPACT THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX-EXEMPT STATUS. THE ORGANIZATION BELIEVES IT HAS APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN, AND AS SUCH, DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX RETURNS FOR THE LAST THREE FISCAL YEARS (OPEN YEARS) ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CEO, CFO, BOARD TREASURER REVIEW THE 990 AND APPROVE PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS. A COPY IS ALSO PROVIDED FOR REVIEW TO THE EXECUTIVE AND FINANCE COMMITTEES FOR COMMENT PRIOR TO APPROVAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS CONSIDERS ANY ITEMS DISCLOSED ANNUALLY AND DETERMINES WHAT ACTION, IF ANY, IS NECESSARY. POSSIBLE ACTIONS INCLUDE FULL DISCLOSURE TO THE BOARD AND OTHER INDIVIDUALS COVERED BY THE POLICY, REQUESTING THE INDIVIDUAL WITH THE CONFLICT TO RECUSE HIMSELF FROM PARTICIPATION IN RELATED DISCUSSIONS OR REQUESTING THE INDIVIDUAL TO RESIGN FROM HIS POSITION WITH THE ORGANIZATION. THE CHAIRMAN AND CHIEF OPERATING OFFICER MONITOR PROPOSED OR ONGOING TRANSACTIONS FOR ANY UNDISCLOSED CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND REPORT TO THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION USES COMPARABILITY DATA FROM HABITAT FOR HUMANITY INTERNATIONAL (HFHI) DURING COMPENSATION REVIEWS. THE HFHI STUDY INCLUDES DETAILED COMPENSATION REPORTS OF VARIOUS POSITION AT LIKE-SIZED AFFILIATES ACROSS THE COUNTRY. THIS DATA IS USED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE TO DETERMINE THE COMPENSATION OF THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFIER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS FORM 990, GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND MOST RECENT AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
